Skoda Auto Starts Planned Summer Production Break, CTK Reports

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-07-25T07:07:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/skoda-auto-starts-planned-summer-production-break-ctk-reports.html
Skoda Auto AS, a unit of  Volkswagen
AG (VOW) , started a planned two-week summer production break at all
its plants,  CTK  reported, citing company spokesman Rudolf
Dreithaler.  Production restarts on Aug. 7 with the exception of the
Fabia model, for which the break will end on Aug. 14, the
newswire added.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  